## .gitignore Selection

**Choose: `Python`** from GitHub's template options.

Here's what you should add to the standard Python .gitignore:
```gitignore
# Additional for Parichay Project

# AWS credentials and config
.aws/
aws-exports.js

# API Keys and sensitive data
.env
.env.local
.env.production
*.key
config/secrets.yml

# Large datasets
*.csv
*.xlsx
!example_data.csv

# AWS CloudFormation outputs
outputs.json
deployment-outputs.json

# Lambda deployment packages
*.zip
deployment-package/

# Local development
local_test_data/
temp_processing/

# IDE specific
.vscode/settings.json
.idea/workspace.xml

# System files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Documentation builds
docs/_build/
docs/site/

# Added by git standards propagation
node_modules/
*.log
dist/
coverage/
*.swp
